		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Ever wonder why some Bards solo?<a name="61953"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 8:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We have this class, that to play well takes more concentration than any other class.  SO we hear from those who have alts...this game is about grouping...soloing is bad.
<br />

<br />
Problem is, just how social can a bard be when grouped?  Do you have time to target, twist, think, move, cc, whatever else you might be doing, AND type??  I am thinking recently, if you want to be social and group....are you really that social to your group when every answer to any question they ask of you is either a hotkeyed yes or no answer, or a short burst of KHGJKJJKHF before you have to get back at your role in the group.
<br />

<br />
I think grouping is fun...not as fun as when I group with a different class, but fun in a different way.  It is never very social though....
<br />

<br />
If you are playing as best you can and have time to actually enjoy the conversation...maybe you are not doing that great a job.  We joke all the time about how bards never answer tells, how we are the strong silent type....really it is just being too busy to do much else when grouped.
<br />

<br />
So what is the difference between solo and small(very small) talk to the guild...vs the same kinda of chat with a group?
<br />

<br />
I believe this is why a fairly large portion of Bards do solo.  The benifits of group play do not benifit our class as much as other classes.  They get decent conversation even.  LOL
<br />

<br />
This is also why this latest nerf targeting the best method we had to gain efficient experience kicks sand in the soloers face.  Of course we can solo, but chanting and charming lowly 57 mobs is soo old hat it is just not worth the mind numbing effort.  Charming kiting inside a dungeon has risk, but outdoors?
<br />

<br />
I have no problems with any type of gameplay.  Done it all, like it all, dismissed some of it as there were better options, adapted to the many nerfs.   However to stand by and hear bards get blasted by their own peers for having area kited...that just can not go untouched.
<br />

<br />
Auto circle was the bad guy here, if there ever was one.  I also still believe some of the greats ever to have played this class....DID area kite at some time, knew how to, and certainly are not cheering about what SONY is doing to us.
<br />

<br />
I truely wish we could be more social when grouped....then again to not twist would be kind of weird.  I talk the same amount grouped as solo...basically not much.  It is a tuff job, but somebody has to be the bard...maybe this is why so few choose the class.  I love the class.
<br />

<br />
Moose
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
