			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ever wonder why some Bards solo?<a name="61955"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 9:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think that if I wanted to be social while soloing, the bard would definitely not have been my first choice.  I'd have gone with a necro or a BL.  Actually, I would have picked one of those two over a bard for ANY sort of soloing because it is much more &quot;mindless&quot; to solo with one of those classes.
<br />

<br />
I agree with your point on bards being non-social.  It's a definite &quot;weakness&quot; to playing one. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
However, you can't call swarm kiting old-hat, and make it all Sony's fault by calling the nerf a slap in the face for all soloers.  You're basing this assumption on how you personally feel about swarm kiting; however, others might feel differently.
<br />

<br />
People play how they want to play; I'm not sure why people feel the need to blast someone else for playing their bard differently.  I'm not saying you are blasting anyone -- in fact, I know you're not -- but now I'm generalizing other posts/attitudes.
<br />

<br />
That is why the class rocks -- there are so many different ways for a bard to do things.  If you loved AE kiting, awesome.  It's gone now, so such is life.  Hopefully, that wasn't the only reason you enjoyed the bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
