				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ever wonder why some Bards solo?<a name="61968"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 11:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I too am concerned about the effect this will have on my bard's viability while soloing.  I'm in a position where my peak playing ours are the low-point of the day; I would AE kite in Dulak and regularly find myself completely alone there for an hour or two.  So, now I'm not sure what I'm going to do; but I will have fun finding out.  I will miss the opportunity to chat so much with my guild while kiting, however.
<br />

<br />
I also have an alt, and I autocircled, so I'm getting a bit tired of all this &quot;those who have alts&quot; and &quot;Auto circle was the bad guy here, if there ever was one&quot; stuff.  Yawn.
<br />

<br />
But, in amongst the prejudicial one-liners, Moose has a decent point.  I'm a little more optimistic, however -- I will work on my epic, try out a couple of the quest guides, maybe even learn to swarm kite.  I'll enjoy just being a bard for a change (and the AE does NOT maketh the bard).  
<br />

<br />
If a player doesn't find that other stuff interesting for them any more, and just wants to grind away forever, I have to wonder why they keep on being a bard.  It's like the antithesis of our class.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It is a tuff job, but somebody has to be the bard...</span></blockquote>
<br />
I wholeheartedly agree!
<br />

<br />
