				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ever wonder why some Bards solo?<a name="62044"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 9:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree with Moose in that the AoE kiting problem is with auto-circle and not AoE dots.  However, I dont think that bards solo because they cant be social in groups.  I soloed for a couple of different reasons - Not enough time to effectively group, not being able to find a group and being able to get consistant experience.  
<br />

<br />
When I group my social commentary depends upon how much demand there is on the group.  Casually fighting somewhere (Seb, PoI, PoV) I chat a lot between pulls.  In more demanding situations - when I pull for example - I wont say anything except &quot;Inc %t&quot;.  In general, if I feel the need to be social I can usually squeeze it in - its just another thing a bard does.</span></td>
