			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ever wonder why some Bards solo?<a name="62399"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 16 04 11:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Moose you hit the nail on the head.
<br />

<br />
I'm a fast typist, so I can usually fire off a decent comment within my 3 seconds of cast time.  But when I'm also pulling, there's no time for anything except the periodic &quot;Move up to me.&quot; (which I really should make a hotkey for)
<br />

<br />
I'm not generally quick of wit (as the person behind the keyboard), but oddly I have been pretty funny in groups as a non bard.  I have had groups say they really enjoyed my presence, even aside from my pretty well developed playing ability (general EQ skills).
<br />

<br />
But as a bard, I'm just an efficiency machine.  Calm, debuff pull, call INC, run back to group, fire haste song, fire mob snare/slow, fire mana song, repeat to haste song, etc.  Mob down to 20%, I run and pull next mob.  And so on.  Granted I could take the 15 seconds as mentioned above and make conversation, but it's very difficult for me to intentionally induce delay during play.  If we're in a med break (rare for groups I lead<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> then chatter is great.
<br />

<br />
Bards, and rogues to a much lesser degree, should be the life of the party so to speak.  We should be the clowns, the buffoons, the fools.  I recall a guild from EMarr server that I used to play on.  I think they were &quot;Drunken Pirates&quot;.  They were crazy, looney, comical.  It was rare to pass by a group of them and not be quickly amused by their antics.  I always envied that.
<br />

<br />
I'm giving up my bard now, for a variety of reasons.  One is that I feel I'm at my pinnacle.  There will probably be no future situation where I'll be able to do more, or to be more valuable to a group.  Most likely my value will decrease the higher I get.  So I might as well switch to a class that has time to entertain the group (as well as myself).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
